# DEPRECATED: This crontab approach has been replaced by scheduler.py
#
# The new scheduler uses APScheduler with Redis persistence, which:
# - Catches up missed runs when the server was offline
# - Coalesces multiple missed runs into one execution
# - Provides better logging and job management
#
# To use the new scheduler:
#   1. Configure jobs in config.ini [schedules] section
#   2. Install the systemd service: docs/lifestream-scheduler.service
#   3. Or run directly: python scheduler.py
#
# Commands:
#   python scheduler.py --list    # List configured jobs
#   python scheduler.py --status  # Show next run times
#   python scheduler.py --run JOB # Run a job immediately
#
# ============================================================================
# Legacy crontab entries (for reference):
# ============================================================================

